Mystery surrounds the shooting of a man at a car wash in Acorn Road, Mariannhill, near Pinetown on Friday. According to Captain Nqobile Gwala, spokesperson for the SAPS in KwaZulu-Natal, two men approached the man at around 12.30 pm. They shot him and then fled. Paramedics from Netcare 911 said that when they arrived at the car wash, they found the man lying in a pool of blood in the driveway. He was declared dead at the scene. Gwala said a case of murder is being investigated by Mariannhill police. The motive remains unknown.